  "prompt": "How much time does Wipro takes to send a DOJ after the background verification is done?",
  "response": "The time it takes for Wipro to issue a Date of Joining (DOJ) after the background verification process can vary. Typically, it can take anywhere from a few days to a couple of weeks, depending on factors such as the volume of candidates, the complexity of individual background checks, and internal HR processes. For the most precise information, it's best to reach out directly to the HR representative or contact person at Wipro who is handling your onboarding process.",
